revision.text:
{{Main|2006 Israel-Gaza conflict}} On 2006-11-16, '''France, Italy and Spain announced a new Middle East peace plan''' proposed by [[Prime Minister of Spain|Spanish Premier]] [[José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero]] during talks with [[President of France|French president]] [[Jacques Chirac]]. Later on, the plan was introduced to [[Romano Prodi]], Italy's prime minister who gave his full support to the plan. The peace move came after [[Israel]] invaded the [[Gaza Strip]] in [[Operation Autumn Clouds]].
